        <h2>How to Rent a Car</h2>
        <h3> Renting a car in Canada involves these basic steps: </h3>
        <ul class="car-rent-ul">
            <li class="car-rent-li">Choose a car rental company.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Select the type of vehicle you want to rent.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Provide the necessary identification and payment method.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Agree to the terms and conditions of the rental agreement.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Inspect the car before driving it off the lot.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to Consider When Renting a Car</h2>
        <h3>Here are some factors you should consider:</h3>
        <ul class="car-rent-ul">
            <li class="car-rent-li">Cost: Rates can vary widely depending on the company, the type of car, and the length of the rental.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Type of vehicle: Consider what size and type of vehicle you need. Larger vehicles tend to cost more to rent.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Insurance: Check if your current auto insurance policy covers rental cars.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Location: Rates can differ based on where you rent the car. Airport locations may charge more.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Requirements for Renting a Car</h2>
        <h3>Most car rental companies require the following:</h3>
        <ul class="car-rent-ul">
            <li class="car-rent-li">Valid driver's license: You must have a valid driver's license that's been in effect for at least one year.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Minimum age: Most companies require renters to be at least 21 years old, though this can vary.</li>
            <li class="car-rent-li">Credit card: You'll need a credit card in your name to cover the security deposit.</li>
        </ul>

